{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_honda_ver02/data/sn85042551/00200294324/1921022701/0572.xml":{"full_text":"tj y\n1\niii\nhat the\nuna now\now is over\nH\nII\nil\nAMARILLO DAILY NEWS, SUNDAY MORNING, FEBRUARY 27, 1921 PART ONE\n-8\n3\nh\nMl\nI\nin\n:-s.u: .if\nt We feel that we have demonstrated to the\npeople that we have a definite place in the affairs\nof Amarjllo and the Plains Country of Texas.\nAt a time when there was every evidence of a\nfinancial and consequent business depression, we\nstaged an event declared by those who are in\nposition to know, to be the best and most thor\nough gloom-dispelling agency ever known in this\nsection. Reference is here made to the Auto\nmobile and Style Shows, held, simultaneously\nwith the annual convention of the Buyers and\nSellers Association.\nIn making this statement about the success of\nthe event just closed we are not arrogating to pur\nselves any of the glory attaching to business men\nin other lines. We accqrd to. them the full measure\nof credit that is theirs, and it is in no mean propor\ntion in rounding out the ultimate scope of success\nachieved.\nHaving reached the conclusion that the de\npression was in large measure psychologicalthe\nAmarillo-Panhandle Automotive Association de\ntermined to set in motion an agency of offset. The\nshow was selected as the medium through which\ngloom might best be dispelled.. This stage of the\ngame reached, announcement was made that we\nvill have a show, (n this cf course, we went on\nthe assumption that we would have the f ull, Kearty\nand unselfish cooperation of the business men in\nother lines. Nor were we disappointed. The other\nbusiness men were back of us, lending their sug\ngestions and support at every turn. We als realiz\ned our need for the cooperation of the cattlemen\nthrough the effective agency of their surpassingly\nactive Buyers and Sellers Association, having\nfrom the first reached the conclusion to hold the?\nShows on the dates of the annual convention of\nthat organization. t\nFor the unqualified success of the Shows, we\nare profoundly grateful to every agency tending\nto make more secure our ambition in connection\nwith the enterprise. We admit our agreeable.sur\nprise not at the success, but in the measure of the,\nsame, crowning our combined efforts. We realize\nthat tlie dissipation of the suggestion jof gloomy\ndepression was not confined to Amarillo, but ex?,\ntended to every community represented, through\nthe citizens present. i\nThrough this enterprise we have dempnstrated\nto all our fellow citizens that we are as unselfishly\ninterested in the progress, the development, the\nadvancement of our own and the communities\nabout us, as are the men engaged in any other lii)e\nof legitimate endeavor. We have shown a sowing\nfor the general good, chancing an incidental reap\ning, taking our share of whatever risk rnay be in\ncurred in such endeavors. i t\nThe automobile and accessory dealer i$ a njajh\nwith a definite mission, a well defined pelcj pf.sep\nvice. The automobile is no longer considered,, by\nthe intelligent citizen, as a luxury-jt Ms Pun\nished the burdens of humanity, eliminated\ngeryj banished distances, created prof its for, it$\nusersj lengthened the lives of the people, addeq l\ntheir pleasures, and furnished legitimate. ai(\nprofitable employment to a ventable army o\nCltizepS.\nHaying assumed responsibility as qizr ,qf\nthis community and in the communities tough\nout this portion of the state of Texas, we feel that\nwe have a rightful part in every development pr(\ngram! of the territory. We feel that w have un\nquestionably shown to our our fellow fitizeps our\ncapacity for service, our ability to plan and execute\nfor the general welfare. We are delighted to have\nreceived the recognition that fras beeaours in pon-r\nriectioh with the Shows, and we are outlining qther\nfeatures of service through which the ntire; peo\nple oj this city and section will be benefitted. t y\nFinally, we wish to formally ihank for. .hearty\nand ynselfish cooperation ,and service The Am?:\nrillq Board of City Development, the Panhandle;-;\nPlains Chamber cf Commerce, Tlie Anprillo Bfl?\nDepartment, the Amarillo Police Department; the\nmodels in.the Style Show, the press of Amrillp\nand the Plains Country, and each nd qyry\nAgency making for the success of the Shows,\nwhether here or elsewhere.\nYours Sincerely,\nMmtirillri-Parihimdle Automotive i\n'lit\n\"I'\nI\nV\nn\n'I\ni\n'4\nH.r i\ntr\nr m\ni\ni\nssocmWkn\nV","height":"28096","width":"20304"}}
